{
  "stem": "12494.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "My-- my uncle studied at the University of Vienna because he couldn't get into a Hungarian university.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Other people went particularly to Italy, they went to France, [INAUDIBLE] all over Europe and they got their degrees and came back and practiced in Hungary-- practiced professions in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But in 1938 was the first year that official discriminatory legislation was established in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And so we felt that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And, of course, '38 was a-- was an eventful year.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Austria was annexed by Germany, I believe in March.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And then came the Czechoslovakian crisis.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I was to be bar mitzvah that year, in 1938.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "My actual bar mitzvah was in the summer, but my parents decided to have the event officially celebrated in the fall, after the holidays, because that was socially better.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And so, in view of the Czechoslovakian crisis, they sent my brother and me to Switzerland for the summer, with the idea that we would be coming back and then there would be the bar mitzvah celebration.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Unfortunately, the Czechoslovakian crisis was not solved by-- solved by the end of the summer.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So they decided to leave us in-- in Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And we actually stayed in Switzerland with a-- with a short interruption until after the-- the war started.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We stayed at the Orthodox Jewish school, a boarding school, [?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Institut ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Ascher, ?] which no longer exists but it existed for many years after the war and for many years before the war.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, my uncle was at [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Institut ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Ascher ?] before World War II.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Before World War I, I'm sorry.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it-- it was a school with some reputation.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A good Jewish school, very Orthodox, satisfied all the religious requirements.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
